(g) is not solely for personal use but also for commercial use;
(h) is designed for professionals and/ or for professional use even if these
Covered Appliance(s) are set and used at Insured Premises;
(j)
(i) is designed to operate without any connection to the main supply;
not belongs to the Insured;
(k) is used in the Insured Premises that has been entrusted, rented or
borrowed.
2. Accessories or peripherals such as cables, dishwasher baskets, oven
accessories, remote controls.
3. Consumables and parts subject to wear & tear (gradual deterioration
associated with the age and use of the Covered Appliance) as described in
